commentTextItems.html: no bowling heroics as Naeem picks a short ball on the leg stump and smashes it past the diving deep square leg fielder for a boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: Bangladesh take a 2-1 lead with this win. Zimbabwe begun well but Masakadza's dismissal put the brakes on when they were seemingly inching towards a total upward of 250. Partnership between Tamim and Ashraful decidedly swung the match in Bangladesh's favour. Stay back for post match quotes
Masakadza says " We were below par with batting and kept losing wickets at regular intervals. We need to work on our batting and we played the spinners well today but we needed to be more decisive "

Shakib says" We tried a few experiments, which did not work. We will try it some other time. If we play to our merits we will win as these are our home conditions. Whenever the top-order scores runs it becomes easier for the middle order"

Tamim Iqbal is the Man of the match. He says" I am not happy because I did not go on to get the century and did not finish my job. The boys are really working hard and am happy with the team's progress. On any given day, the team that plays better cricket will win the match"
That's it from all of us here at Cricinfo and do remember to join us on tueday for the fourth ODI, which starts at 10:30 am local time

dismissalComment.html: short and wide outside the off stump and Taylor gives his all and looks to cut through the off side, gets the edge and through to Rahim behind the wicket, Bangladesh have the first breakthrough in Taylor.

dismissalText.long: c Naeem Islam b Enamul Haque jnr
dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry c Naeem Islam b Enamul Haque jnr 29 (29b 2x4 2x6 32m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: outside the off stump. Coventry moves across and looks to drag it away to midwicket again but Enamul notices it early and pitches it fuller. Coventry manages a top-edge which is taken comfortably by Naeem at midwicket. Good time to get the wicket for Bangladesh

dismissalText.commentary: Forster Mutizwa c Mahmudullah b Enamul Haque jnr 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: another left armer doing the trick for Bangladesh today. Mutizwa looks to clear the outfield without getting under the delivery and holes out to long-off. Poor cricket by Zimbabwe here

dismissalText.long: c Raqibul Hasan b Abdur Razzak
dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Raqibul Hasan b Abdur Razzak 84 (79b 12x4 1x6 95m) SR: 106.32

dismissalComment.html: a long hop and Masakadaza falls to a tame shot, pulls straight to Raqibul at midwicket and he trudges off slowly back to the pavilion, he could have hit that ball to any corner of the ground for a boundary.

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller b Mahmudullah 27 (44b 2x4 0x6 45m) SR: 61.36

dismissalComment.html: drags it a touch short  and flatter as he sees Waller coming down the track and he pushes forward and gets beaten and the ball knocks the stumps.

headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Abdur Razzak 5 (8b 1x4 0x6 14m) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: another tame dismissal, tosses it up outside the off stump and Matsikenyeri cuts and gets an inside edge onto the stumps. The Zimbabwe innings is falling apart.

dismissalComment.html: and there's the wicket as Chibhabha falls for a needless shot as he drags one on the off stump straight into the hands of Naeem at midwicket

dismissalComment.html: top-edge! Gets a top-edge on the cut shot and a good catch taken by Enamul at third man

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal st †Taylor b Cremer 80 (72b 10x4 2x6 98m) SR: 111.11
